<BaseLayout
  title="Contact — Journal Foundation"
  description="How to reach the Journal Foundation — developers, advisors, funders, press, and security."
>
  <h1>Contact</h1>
  <p class="lead">
    We’re early. If you’re a privacy-minded <strong>developer</strong>, <strong>researcher</strong>,
    <strong>advisor</strong>, or <strong>funder</strong>, we’d love to hear from you.
  </p>

  <h2>Primary Channels</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>General &amp; Partnerships:</strong>
      <a
        href="mailto:hello@journalfoundation.org?subject=General%20and%20partnership%20inquiry"
      >
        hello@journalfoundation.org
      </a>
      <br />
      Short proposals, partnership ideas, intros.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Specs &amp; Engineering:</strong>
      <a
        href="mailto:specs@journalfoundation.org?subject=Specifications%20or%20engineering%20question"
      >
        specs@journalfoundation.org
      </a>
      ·
      <a
        href="https://github.com/journalfoundation/discussions"
        target="_blank"
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
      >
        GitHub Discussions →
      </a>
      <br />
      Protocol/RFC feedback, reference impl questions.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Press &amp; Speaking:</strong>
      <a
        href="mailto:press@journalfoundation.org?subject=Press%20inquiry"
      >
        press@journalfoundation.org
      </a>
      <br />
      Media, interviews, event invitations.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Funding &amp; Grants:</strong>
      <a
        href="mailto:grants@journalfoundation.org?subject=Funding%20or%20grants%20inquiry"
      >
        grants@journalfoundation.org
      </a>
      <br />
      Philanthropy, research grants, programmatic support.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Community &amp; Code</h2>
  <p>
    <strong>GitHub Discussions:</strong>
    <a
      href="https://github.com/journalfoundation/discussions"
      target="_blank"
      rel="noopener noreferrer"
    >
      github.com/journalfoundation/discussions
    </a>
    — best for public questions, RFC debates, and roadmap ideas.
  </p>

  <h2>Security</h2>
  <p>
    Report vulnerabilities to
    <a
      href="mailto:security@journalfoundation.org?subject=Security%20vulnerability%20report"
    >
      security@journalfoundation.org
    </a>.
    Encrypt mail with our PGP key:
  </p>
  <pre><code>Fingerprint: 0000 0000 0000 0000 0000  0000 0000 0000 0000 0000
Key: https://journalfoundation.org/pgp/security.asc</code></pre>
  <p>We publish a <code>/.well-known/security.txt</code> per RFC 9116.</p>

  <h2>Tips (Optional)</h2>
  <p>
    For sensitive outreach you may use Signal: <strong>+1-XXX-XXX-XXXX</strong>. Be aware Signal shares
    your number with us; a secondary number is fine.
  </p>

  <h2>Response Policy</h2>
  <p>We triage weekly. Security reports are prioritized and acknowledged within 72 hours.</p>

  <h2>Privacy</h2>
  <p>No forms. No trackers. Email us or open a public thread; we don’t harvest or sell contact data.</p>

